  "texts": [
    "In the FinBERT model [44], based on the BERT architecture, using a span of MLM, the data is a mixture of a general corpus and financial domain.",
    "FinBERT outperformed models trained only on general language in financial sentiment analysis.",
    "The mixed-domain approach makes sense when the data is less abundant.In some cases, it makes sense to do continued training, which is adding either more training with domain-specific data or adding adapters.",
    "Instead of modifying the matrix parameters, or the weights, the adapters are small initialized weights that are added at every layer of the transformer architecture.",
    "Adapters modules [32,6,56] are incredibly efficient at adding domain-specific knowledge for both LLMs and RoBERTa."
  ],
